Package model

Interface GameEngine

  • All Superinterfaces:
    GameCallbackCollection
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GameEngineImpl
    public interface GameEngine
extends GameCallbackCollection
    The main interface in Further Programming Assignment.

    This interface should be implemented as GameEngineImpl which has a no argument constructor. All the methods in the interface need to be carefully implemented as per the Javadoc below.

    Author:
    Ross Nye
    See Also:
    GameCallbackCollection, Player, Bet, Hand, Deck

      • addPlayer

        void addPlayer​(Player player)
        throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
               java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Adds supplied player to the Game Engine. The supplied player must be valid player with a unique ID; if the ID already exists the add should be rejected and an exception thrown (see below).

        Hint: The unique ID should be enforced here and not in PlayerImpl class

        Parameters:
        player - the player to be added to the Game Engine
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the player parameter is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if a player with the same ID as the player supplied in the parameter already exists in the Game Engine
        See Also:
        Player

      • placeBet

        void placeBet​(java.lang.String playerId,
              int amount)
       throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
              java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Places a score bet of the supplied amount for the player who's id matches the supplied playerId.

        A bet can replace an existing bet if its bet amount is greater than the existing bet.

        Parameters:
        playerId - the id of the Player who placed the bet
        amount - the amount the was bet
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - is thrown if the playerId parameter is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - is thrown in the following cases
        • There is no current player with the supplied playerId
        • The supplied amount is not a positive number
        • The supplied player is does not have enough points to place the bet
        • If, when replacing an existing bet, the bet amount is not greater the existing bet
        See Also:
        Bet, ScoreBet

      • dealPlayer

        void dealPlayer​(java.lang.String playerId,
                int delay)
         throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                java.lang.IllegalStateException
        Deals a hand to the specified player.

        Cards are dealt to the specified player in the following manner

        • a card is removed from the deck and dealt to the player
        • a delay occurs, of the specified time in ms, between the card being removed from the deck and it being dealt to the player
          • if the card does not bust in player's hand:
            • the GameCallback.playerCard(Player, model.card.Card) is invoked on all the GameCallback objects that have been registered, notifying the player and the card dealt (all get the same information!)
            • the process is then repeated for the next card until a bust occurs
          • if the card does bust in the player's hand
            • the GameCallback.playerBust(Player, model.card.Card) is invoked on all the GameCallback objects that have been registered, notifying the player and the card that was attempted to be dealt to the player

        Note: A bust card is burnt, and not returned to the deck or dealt to any subsequent player.

        Parameters:
        playerId - the id of the Player who placed the bet
        delay - the delay in milliseconds prior to each card being dealt
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the supplied playerId is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - in the following cases
        • there is no current player with the supplied playerId
        • the supplied delay is a negative number
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - in the following cases
        • if the player with the supplied playerId has not placed a bet
        • if the player with the supplied playerId has already been dealt to

      • dealHouse

        void dealHouse​(int delay)
        throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Deals a hand to the House using the same procedure as outlined in dealPlayer(String, int)

        The GameCallback.houseCard(model.card.Hand, model.card.Card) and GameCallback.houseBust(model.card.Hand, model.card.Card) methods are used in place of the player based callback methods.

        Important: Prior to invoking GameCallback.houseBust(model.card.Hand, model.card.Card) all the bets must applied so the correct information is available to the callbacks.

        Parameters:
        delay - the delay in milliseconds prior to each card being dealt
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the supplied delay is a negative number

      • resetAllBetsAndHands

        void resetAllBetsAndHands()
        Resets all bets for all the players in the Game Engine.

        As each player's bet is reset and all the registered GameCallback objects should be notified of the updated bet using the GameCallback.betUpdated(Player) callback method. After the bets for each player is reset the player's hand should also be reset in order be ready for a new hand to be dealt to the player.

        Note: Bets should be reset for all players by the client after a spin.

        See Also:
        Player.resetBet()
